  "body": "In kubelet/dockertools/manager.go:\n\nIn [`SyncPod()`](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L1911-L1956), when a container fails to be restarted, we'll store the error reason in the reason cache, and set the container to `Waiting` state in `GetPodStatus()`.\n\nBut in [`GetPodStatus()`](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L519-L531), when there are historical containers (which means that the corresponding `statuses` will be set in the loop above), only container with `kubecontainer.ErrCrashLoopBackOff.Error()` is set to `Waiting`, while the container fails with other reasons will be set to `Terminated` because of the historical exited containers.\n\nIs this the expected behavior?\n\n/cc @yujuhong @dchen1107 \n",
